article.description: — Cameron Tyson had 26 points as Seattle topped Morgan State 93-80 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Tyson scores 26 to lift Seattle past Morgan St. 93-80
article.linkText: Tyson scores 26 to lift Seattle past Morgan St. 93-80
article.story: SEATTLE -- — Cameron Tyson had 26 points as Seattle topped Morgan State 93-80 on Thursday night. Darrion Trammell had 16 points and six assists for Seattle (3-1). Kobe Williamson added 14 points and seven rebounds. Emeka Udenyi had 12 points. Riley Grigsby, the Redhawks' leading scorer coming into the matchup at 18 points per game, scored only 5 points on 2-of-10 shooting. Isaiah Burke had 19 points for the Bears (2-2). Keith McGee added 16 points. Will Thomas had 15 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
